This paper deals with the capacity of a communication channel, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT). The channel model considered in the paper involves a binary state, which is a common feature in control systems (cs.SY). The use of modulo2 addition in the channel state is also a common feature in digital signal processing and coding theory (cs.NI). The paper derives closed form expressions for the capacity and channel input distribution, which involves optimization and mathematical analysis (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of feedback and transmission cost, which are relevant topics in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
